messages.message:
I’m getting this error while starting `grpc-file-service` any ideas?
```ERROR - Could not start service - grpc-file-service. Error=b"/Users/youssef/Work/instabase/core-services/file-tservice/grpc-file-service/../../../shared-utils/build-utils/shared/build-go-service.mk:47: warning: overriding commands for target `run-test'
/Users/youssef/Work/instabase/core-services/file-tservice/grpc-file-service/../../../shared-utils/build-utils/shared/build-go.mk:42: warning: ignoring old commands for target `run-test'
Unable to find image 'instabase/grpc-file-service:latest' locally
docker: Error response from daemon: pull access denied for instabase/grpc-file-service, repository does not exist or may require 'docker login': denied: requested access to the resource is denied.
See 'docker run --help'.
make: *** [run-docker] Error 125
" ```
Can you share what command you used to start the service?
I'm also getting the same error when running `python provisioner.py start grpc-file-service --as-docker`

I get the error when I use
`python provisioner.py start grpc-file-service --use-prebuilt --as-docker`
but when I use
`python provisioner.py start grpc-file-service` it says
```INFO - Started the service - grpc-file-service  in local mode. Output logs are redirected to core-services/file-tservice/grpc-file-service/grpc-file-service.log
INFO - Check the status using : provisioner.py status grpc-file-service```
But the service never really starts
```INFO - Service=grpc-file-service               status=Down. Please see core-services/file-tservice/grpc-file-service/grpc-file-service.log for details```
Thanks Youssef! Can you try navigating to core-services/file-tservice/grpc-file-service and running `make build-docker run-docker` ?
Do `docker login` as mentioned in the error message?

@Nidhi that didn’t work, it gave me this error and the service didn’t start
```../../../../../build/go/src/instabase/storage/mountservice/mountservice.go:3931:8: undefined: thrift.ResponseMeta
../../../../../build/go/src/instabase/storage/mountservice/mountservice.go:3956:50: undefined: thrift.ResponseMeta
../../../../../build/go/src/instabase/storage/mountservice/mountservice.go:3960:56: undefined: thrift.ResponseMeta
../../../../../build/go/src/instabase/storage/mountservice/mountservice.go:216:32: too many errors
mv: cannot stat '/go/src/instabase/core-services/file-tservice/grpc-file-service/src/go/src/instabase/fileservice/main': No such file or directory
make: *** [build-docker] Error 1```
However I tried `docker login` as @Mohit suggested and it starts now when I run it as prebuilt. But I can swear that I tried `docker login` before and it didn’t help :lolcry:
Thank y’all for helping!!
